# Copy to `.env` for local development. Do not commit real values.
# See README.md → Environment variables for Cloudflare Workers + Vite build-time notes.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Browser (Vite) — embedded in the client bundle at BUILD time
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required for `npm run build` and `npm run dev`. The publishable (anon) key is
# safe to ship in client JS; never put the service role key in VITE_* vars.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your-supabase-publishable-key

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare Worker / TanStack Start server runtime
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Set the same values in the Worker (Dashboard → Workers → Settings → Variables,
# or `wrangler secret put` / `wrangler vars` as appropriate). Used by server
# code paths such as Supabase auth middleware (see `auth-middleware.ts`).
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your-supabase-publishable-key

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase Edge Functions (local CLI — not the Cloudflare Worker)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Edge Functions locally use `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` by default from the Supabase CLI.
# It can match the publishable/anon key used as SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY.
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-publishable-key

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Server/admin only — never VITE_* or browser
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used only if server code imports `supabaseAdmin` from `client.server.ts`.
# This repo does not currently use that client in routes; Supabase Edge
# Functions use their own secrets. Do not expose in the browser.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-supabase-service-role-key
